article.headline: Drake 69, Indiana State 66
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Chaun Brooks and Joshua Robinson each scored 10 points to lead Drake over Indiana State 69-66 Wednesday. The Bulldogs (9-10, 5-6 Missouri Valley Conference) led 61-48 with 6:56 left when Indiana State went on a 13-2 run to close the gap to 63-61 with 2:18 to play. Lonnie Randolph's steal and layup made it 65-61 before the Sycamores' Wilfred Antoine cut the lead to two. Klayton Korver sank a long 3-pointer to extend Drake's lead to 68-63 lead before Eric Gray, who led all scorers with 25 points, sank his own 3-pointer. Randolph made one of two free throws and the Sycamores missed three 3-point attempts as time ran out. The Sycamores (8-11, 4-7) were playing without leading scorer David Moss who was suspended from the team pending charges of domestic abuse. The Bulldogs jumped out to a 17-4 lead making five straight shots early in the game and never looked back. Drake, which ranks fourth in the nation in steals, had eight in the first half and finished the game with 11. The Sycamores, who finished just 4-7 from the foul line, didn't attempt a free throw in the first half while the Bulldogs went 21-32 from the line.
